 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Sr Director, Data Science Lowe's 45,344 reviews Charlotte, NC 28202 Full-time Lowe's 45,344 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Key Responsibilities 
 Effectively manage the highly qualified team of Data-Scientists and motivate to deliver useful solutions. Hire top talent, create effective team structure and mentor managers to create high-performance Data-Science team within the organization. Deliver innovative data solutions that utilize Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, statistical and quantitative modeling approaches. Collaborate with cross-functional groups, stakeholders, and senior leadership to ensure alignment and understand business needs to deliver actionable insights for ways Lowe's can more effectively capitalize on new consumers and existing consumers Expand and evangelize best practices for scoping, building, validating, deploying, and monitoring data science products. Educate both internal and external stakeholders at all levels to drive implementation and adoption Partner with Product, Engineering, Sales, Administration and Operations leadership to formulate roadmaps, influence decision making, and drive prioritization Find opportunities for improvement across the business and assist in decision-making across teams Hires, trains, and develops talent for growth opportunities; monitors team/individual’s morale and engagement to maintain highly effective and collaborative environments; drives the talent strategy and best practices across the team Responsible for departmental budget and forecasting decisions, and budget allocation; ensures technical solutions are delivered and maintained in a cost-effective manner 
Required Qualifications 
Bachelors Degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Physics, Economics, Engineering, Computer Science, Data or Information Science, or related quantitative analytic field (or equivalent work experience in a related field) 
12 Years of Data Science experience (fewer years may be accepted with a Masters or Doctorate degree) 
7 Years of experience leading a large team of analytics professionals in retail, technology or other customer driven organization 
5 Years of experience interacting with executive and senior stakeholders 
 
Preferred Qualifications 
Masters Degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Physics, Economics, Engineering, Computer Science, Data or Information Science, or related quantitative analytic field 
Deep experience in leading data science teams at scale in a B2C organization 
Previous hands-on experience in production big data and machine learning environments at scale 
Demonstrated ability to balance competing interests in a complex technical and retail environment 
Successful experience leveraging opensource technologies 
Expertise with forecasting, computer vision techniques 
Experience in deploying machine learning algorithms and advanced modeling solutions 
Strong background in Python, TensorFlow, Keras, SQL, CI/CD, data warehousing 
Experience in developing advanced Data Science and ML infrastructure and systems 
Experience with data warehouses, BI platforms, scripting languages, cloud technologies 
